  "Tabular"]], "Input",ExpressionUUID->"2faf73df-4968-3b4d-805d-f105233b7516"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Possible Issues", "Chapter",ExpressionUUID->"59d6a88a-3ae9-404d-b703-916b56f20005"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Aggregation required for collections",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEEComputePixels", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "462f1e62-6bb2-ac47-8812-b879a1796b59"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEImage", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "f6d4de60-9b10-cc47-b424-9a6471c24e1e"],
 ", and similar functions require a single image. A collection pipeline must \
end with ",
 Cell["GEEMosaic", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "9b0227af-703c-c941-bf1d-7fa88e038b57"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEMedian", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "feb7c53f-f08a-0746-9937-4a69be5e5ba6"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEMean", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "8f63bb8c-f72d-684a-8ad4-b0f40b5fd12d"],
 ", or ",
 Cell["GEEFirst", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "4e64351d-3d8b-4840-8e51-f422c4c7d417"],
 " to produce a single image."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"f4ecb399-8180-fa4e-be32-b417412b893a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Band name suffixes with GEEMedian/GEEMean",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": The ",
 Cell["ImageCollection.reduce", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "6c898d8d-02a1-9040-a2a8-80808daab332"],
 " operation used by ",
 Cell["GEEMedian", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "572cc63e-ec12-824c-91fa-ca3ec6800dd3"],
 " and ",
 Cell["GEEMean", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "2b3f6580-fa31-0e4b-b71b-5c00ab34d61e"],
 " appends ",
 Cell["_median", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c599dd51-2800-7840-84ca-cc97f3f3b415"],
 " or ",
 Cell["_mean", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "6e0d387b-9384-f44d-9ebd-0a696f829452"],
 " to band names (e.g., ",
 Cell["\"B4\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "9859a3f0-783b-8741-8413-a9fd173b78e7"],
 " becomes ",
 Cell["\"B4_median\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "6e41f407-af6e-b441-ac09-5a2fb24b7ae3"],
 "). This generally does not affect rendering but may matter if subsequent \
operations reference bands by name."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"a8f5e92e-d5b0-3245-a3bf-0e44450e3749"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Band names with GEEMosaic",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEEMosaic", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "92317aa7-6d2f-544c-b1bc-1a06854a1df7"],
 " preserves original band names. Prefer ",
 Cell["GEEMosaic", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "7bb123c8-71fc-3741-b966-0a024411d494"],
 " when band name preservation is important."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5a649207-8ee2-ff4f-880d-425520d07022"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Heterogeneous band structures",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Some collections (e.g., Sentinel-2) changed their band structure over \
time. Always filter by date and optionally by bounds before selecting bands \
to avoid errors from mismatched bands across images."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"26ea3dac-0ba8-c846-896a-f5593f4c69c1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Filter order for performance",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": While filters can technically be applied in any order, applying date and \
spatial filters first reduces the number of images that subsequent operations \
must process. This improves performance and avoids timeouts on large \
collections."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5dc6f198-d632-924a-94fa-ec8b49c27f06"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEESelectBands on collections",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEESelectBands", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "af10de2d-b544-9345-a8b3-45b87e0c0d1c"],
 " automatically detects whether the input is a collection or a single image \
and uses the appropriate API call (",
 Cell["Collection.map", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "6eb3ee59-7b87-0e40-8c27-9161d8428e62"],
 " with ",
 Cell["Image.select", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "e03aba54-a0c6-4940-ab63-7cb7a40b8d70"],
 " for collections, or ",
 Cell["Image.select", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "864d9f8f-5e7b-b641-b5d2-6b2496dfced4"],
 " directly for images)."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"31576e6b-c8a5-0443-be12-40effdaf6d7f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEFilterBounds region must cover the output area",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": When using ",
 Cell["GEEFilterBounds", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c00aae70-cad7-1b4e-a255-8d07df36c7ac"],
 " with ",
 Cell["GEEComputePixels", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "3b82d93a-5f78-5444-bcac-03be34cbbeb1"],
 ", the filter region should cover at least the same area as the ",
 Cell["GEEComputePixels", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "9fd5dde6-9c84-9641-a24f-41632130b4f3"],
 " bounding box, otherwise the result may contain gaps. ",
 Cell["GEEFilterBounds", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "04649ecd-e0ca-584c-8183-1d1c70dfe8d0"],
 " accepts a bounding box ",
 Cell["{west, south, east, north}", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "454a8862-d45f-e643-9f8a-04bd79864c26"],
 ", any geo primitive (",
 Cell["Entity", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "5c2fcff0-32c3-7e46-baf8-9e278f95879a"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GeoDisk", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "f0574ce6-bdb5-7b44-bf16-fbb258597ff7"],
 ", ",
 Cell["Polygon", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "323df9a2-2bb9-1943-8c70-b987b32d9ad0"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GeoPosition", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "69b60c0d-fbbf-e449-9d67-b6977a42f36d"],
 ", etc.), or a list of primitives \[LongDash] the bounding box is computed \
automatically via ",
 Cell["GeoBoundingBox", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "a47f8247-5c22-354e-9084-a4fb5cc2ec3e"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"1820f988-70fd-1548-8ba3-34c71ee63731"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Common metadata properties",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Use ",
 Cell["GEEGetAssetInfo", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "ea759ab5-68cc-5646-b0ec-f8dd1d4fb4b9"],
 " to discover available metadata properties for any asset. Properties vary \
by dataset -- ",
 Cell["\"CLOUDY_PIXEL_PERCENTAGE\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "2fbd86dd-d70d-9a4a-99d3-12bb088f31c2"],
 " is Sentinel-2 specific while ",
 Cell["\"CLOUD_COVER\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "8e7d0093-f156-7847-a922-e9a749da8bef"],
 " is used by Landsat."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"95be15d2-4f13-ed48-82af-1dfdd4fe0163"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Band name suffixes with NormalizedDifference",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": After ",
 Cell["GEEMedian", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "fc153228-9cf3-b545-96e7-cb6a2fca496d"],
 " or ",
 Cell["GEEMean", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "6cfab250-7edf-1049-b486-9d386eb2a26d"],
 ", band names are suffixed (e.g., ",
 Cell["\"B8\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c9b41050-a069-e545-bf40-d932606c160f"],
 " becomes ",
 Cell["\"B8_median\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "0b432d17-39c3-ac4b-a288-fe7ecee8d134"],
 "). When chaining ",
 Cell["GEENormalizedDifference", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "93fa3065-b678-8246-9ab6-b31d754975cc"],
 " after an aggregation, use the suffixed band names: ",
 Cell["GEENormalizedDifference[{\"B8_median\", \"B4_median\"}]", "InlineCode",
  ExpressionUUID->"48fc16ea-7782-ca4c-8148-1bf8f52c55ec"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7b35f4be-f40c-e34b-9347-80a0a72c0aaf"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEAdd/Subtract/Multiply/Divide with numbers",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": When passing a numeric constant as the second argument, it is \
automatically wrapped as a ",
 Cell["constantValue", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "3fcf3bfb-ee6b-5d48-adc4-0fea31ebe3dc"],
 ". When passing an image expression, it is used directly. Both forms work \
with the ",
 Cell["//", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "9a99fe55-a654-db4d-abbe-9337d7640ed2"],
 " operator."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7146446f-4fab-a648-96e3-3b149dad1d80"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEExpression binding names",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Variable names in the expression string must exactly match the keys in \
the bindings Association. Each binding maps to a single band selected from \
the input image. Multi-band expressions require one binding per band."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"2b1ca3d8-ba44-544e-87b8-3d26fc585100"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEClip geometry",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": The geometry argument must be a GEE geometry expression (from ",
 Cell["GEEGeometry", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "4c1534cc-4f5f-6942-ad7b-595c764360d2"],
 " or a geometry builder), not a raw list of coordinates. Use ",
 Cell["GEEGeometry[{west, south, east, north}]", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "d7a3ef70-5580-7c41-b6b8-53aba99bf965"],
 " to create a rectangle."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"60119fa8-23ec-5f46-8d07-4a8903e06cf7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEUnmask default",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEEUnmask[image]", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "7377e9a1-8cdc-ee44-b801-094a6392e22f"],
 " with no value argument defaults to replacing masked pixels with 0. Use ",
 Cell["GEEUnmask[image, value]", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "493bb184-4bdf-764b-8b04-517b783590b4"],
 " for a custom fill value."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"722dd4ee-9831-604c-9a63-462ed963fe98"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Reducer band name suffixes",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEECollectionMax", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "01a822e4-1cfa-ea47-96e1-5bf7e171be7c"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEECollectionMin", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "2dccb0c5-5140-b446-9604-b7dc87fabf88"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEECollectionSum", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "ef8bd0ac-7db2-484a-9661-fa8bdcab1e0b"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEReduceStdDev", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "688c9b4e-b446-7e45-a507-b99dd85f0771"],
 ", and ",
 Cell["GEEReduceCount", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c324bd35-237c-ba4d-9bf8-4e7e7c29d67c"],
 " use ",
 Cell["ImageCollection.reduce", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "a0848935-fc1e-b949-a465-115bb7577944"],
 " internally and append suffixes (",
 Cell["_max", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "76502d08-768f-2740-94f0-092f175d8e54"],
 ", ",
 Cell["_min", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "60585235-bfc6-9e49-a58b-46f59587f2c8"],
 ", ",
 Cell["_sum", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "8e585d4a-706d-8b45-a03e-6a7d0584204e"],
 ", ",
 Cell["_stdDev", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "4635dd87-633d-4040-8492-d6c3744161b1"],
 ", ",
 Cell["_count", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "6ebe462b-158e-3d45-8dc3-8cba3b429b71"],
 ") to band names. Use the suffixed names when referencing bands downstream."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"c3ddf488-764c-fb46-9f09-8782214240c8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEReducePercentile band names",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Percentile reduction creates bands named ",
 Cell["{bandName}_p{percentile}", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "0eb57f0a-2a59-be4b-9f3e-d9b82efee4ab"],
 " (e.g., ",
 Cell["\"B4_p10\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "b2d45d26-10a2-b840-9cb5-e35582dee124"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"B4_p90\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "a99cfa19-9436-0c4f-bc81-6b682a147ba3"],
 "). The exact suffix depends on the percentile values passed."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"07045cf5-4f87-4c42-8be8-5eeceba482f6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEECollectionMap function argument",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": The function passed to ",
 Cell["GEECollectionMap", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "e0043f20-4000-a746-b9ed-b12318c76f84"],
 " receives an expression tree node (Association), not raw pixel data. It \
must return an expression tree. Use existing helpers (e.g., ",
 Cell["GEENormalizedDifference", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "a2ce1ce3-113c-804b-bc8e-8406d51e796c"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEESelectBands", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "0cc504ba-f783-0148-86fb-f9732e963ff0"],
 ") inside the function body."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9d124b6c-fa64-3f42-8e40-b946456a8345"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEWhere replaces only where test is true",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEEWhere[image, test, value]", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "811fdafd-1228-9447-a995-1a0c49c49ab1"],
 " keeps original pixel values where ",
 Cell["test", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "efa7e155-11eb-9c45-9762-5f77dfff8b94"],
 " is 0 and replaces with ",
 Cell["value", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "61cb8e8e-dd41-f94c-9f9a-ac4651ae2ea0"],
 " where ",
 Cell["test", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "3d827b7b-e894-5146-8c72-bf948094689b"],
 " is non-zero. This is different from ",
 Cell["GEEUpdateMask", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "ff1ff094-e357-2c41-8c33-6571fc349975"],
 ", which masks (removes) pixels rather than replacing them."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"bc1d8906-1a35-564b-9945-2d93b138cc19"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEMerge band structure",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Both collections passed to ",
 Cell["GEEMerge", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "161df533-1b85-d54d-a6da-73d60d7bd20a"],
 " should have the same band structure. Merging collections with different \
bands may cause errors during aggregation."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"dc62bffe-ffaa-4e4c-89da-4346dcbc8474"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEETerrain output bands",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEETerrain", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "542acfd9-025d-3d4a-afb9-7cad43c4d6d5"],
 " produces a multi-band image with bands ",
 Cell["\"slope\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "8f38dea0-dc56-2d4e-9d74-135c64d0674f"],
 " (degrees), ",
 Cell["\"aspect\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "61d928e7-79d5-704a-84a7-9c8862afa254"],
 " (degrees from north), and ",
 Cell["\"hillshade\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c9a19abc-6775-874b-824e-2d171bd4f29f"],
 " (0--255). Use ",
 Cell["GEESelectBands", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "1199658c-47f3-fe47-aa22-8ca18dd70143"],
 " to extract the band you need."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"90cdbf1c-e43e-7c45-820c-2218ca73cc58"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Focal operation radius units",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": All focal operations (",
 Cell["GEEFocalMean", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "33f50a1c-abd9-474e-b91c-5347bed99787"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEFocalMax", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "57caed45-7514-c24a-9474-6c2ad4ca2692"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEFocalMin", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "a3b1ecee-303c-494f-8718-e408f163d101"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEFocalMedian", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c09cd435-16e6-0a49-8fab-de39713fd285"],
 ") use meters as the radius unit. The actual kernel size depends on the \
image's pixel resolution."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"f5bcfc5f-ab19-3945-b6e3-38bbcfce5510"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEReproject caution",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Reprojecting forces computation at a specific scale and can cause \
performance issues if the scale is much finer than the source data. Use \
sparingly and only when projection consistency is required."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"70e66183-933d-0049-8f3d-a90cc8be0e77"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEResample must precede reprojection",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEEResample", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "a031c611-5653-a24c-a317-471e1b7dbe2f"],
 " sets the resampling method for the ",
 StyleBox["next",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " reprojection. Apply it before ",
 Cell["GEEReproject", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "ff49a5b5-1911-a240-b174-a83d3e2ce56b"],
 " or before a function that triggers reprojection."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"4e1dff28-c9e3-7f40-9821-f5835dd990e1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEPixelArea and GEEPixelLonLat take no arguments",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": These are zero-argument constructors that create synthetic images. They \
are not applied to an existing image \[LongDash] use ",
 Cell["GEEAddBands", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "0d91a4d2-53ae-9a46-a4a0-32d699f70c6f"],
 " to combine them with other data."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"25e582a2-a6b6-e746-a4f3-60472fc818b7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEConstant creates a global image",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEEConstant[value]", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "cd43d984-4232-0442-8558-36a5f6b7de5a"],
 " creates an image covering the entire globe. Clip or mask it before using \
with ",
 Cell["GEEComputePixels", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "5a4c1148-e294-0543-98aa-201cfa5a7825"],
 " to avoid processing unnecessary area."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"168c6434-18b6-1d44-a210-779452c9def6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEELog and GEELog10 domain",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Logarithm functions produce ",
 Cell["NaN", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "4f8219c4-de13-524b-802f-5aa7d09c62a7"],
 " for zero or negative pixel values. Ensure the input image has positive \
values, or mask non-positive pixels first."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"da8a57ea-079f-b044-bcfe-28cc7fcd6ffa"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEPow/GEEMod with numbers",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Like other binary image math, the second argument is automatically \
wrapped as a ",
 Cell["constantValue", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "184473f9-d895-0948-98fd-01a0def4fe53"],
 " if numeric. Both image-image and image-number forms are supported."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"178fff40-bfeb-cd40-b89b-547367fba5e9"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEPolygon coordinate order",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Coordinates are ",
 Cell["{lon, lat}", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "5ce59635-f0b9-694c-a727-11263a4cb26c"],
 " pairs (GeoJSON order), not ",
 Cell["{lat, lon}", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "2f0ab70b-8952-c641-9d6c-6a84c0e6052e"],
 ". The polygon is automatically closed \[LongDash] do not repeat the first \
coordinate."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d5d47413-e116-1645-a74f-09c3c4bcf6ff"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEBuffer distance sign",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Positive distance expands the geometry, negative distance shrinks it. A \
point buffered by a positive distance produces a circle."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"03dfadfd-023e-d648-a132-2d17fe1ab786"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEArea returns square meters",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Divide by ",
 Cell["10^6", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "2819e0c5-f96b-974b-83e1-6d6c47c783e7"],
 " for square kilometers or by ",
 Cell["4047", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "4821602d-8835-fd4d-b889-3f4d0362a767"],
 " for acres."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"b4b2e32b-8518-5947-ba25-455ace288b65"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEECast type strings",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Valid type strings include ",
 Cell["\"float\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "1f453236-eecc-e641-af3a-6a7f4b302251"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"double\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "94a1d9ca-d80e-7940-b131-aff3910b4929"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"int8\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "5e2fbec4-aafc-934a-8d7e-7dc86fe8b2f2"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"int16\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "89351df8-ea5f-0947-a179-da1fe5d397a0"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"int32\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "b0619489-6369-124b-ac47-e9d6aa99515d"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"int64\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "09d7af36-eab3-ee4c-9e5b-b401c5b755f6"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"byte\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "1af26385-9404-b642-8eab-ed1ba1ef698d"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"uint8\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "7754ea87-2e4a-7d49-a699-e690b8dab82b"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"uint16\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "e21c2ffb-4035-9e4d-9d4f-7256fcf8bc52"],
 ", ",
 Cell["\"uint32\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "c756f7af-f47e-0742-8126-2382a48675e9"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"deee79ec-b688-674f-a1bc-b7eb471f6502"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEToFloat/GEEToInt affect all bands",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": These convenience functions convert every band. Use ",
 Cell["GEECast", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "02eee253-0198-9b44-abf7-3b4da8a518d3"],
 " for selective band type conversion."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"d6b21946-51d3-e74c-a072-3b7ab82de42a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Join condition expressions",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": ",
 Cell["GEEJoinSimple", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "0a35bae7-14c2-7f49-8704-1335d94a45a0"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEJoinInner", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "71190e75-d68c-c34d-b2e3-9f32f940149b"],
 ", ",
 Cell["GEEJoinSaveBest", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "e4bd1e54-97c4-9549-b52d-c35616856b43"],
 ", and ",
 Cell["GEEJoinSaveAll", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "52bef587-9a61-4146-9a59-9a4a01eeb977"],
 " require a filter condition as a raw GEE expression tree (Association). \
There are no built-in helpers for join filters yet \[LongDash] construct them \
manually using ",
 Cell["\"functionInvocationValue\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "511cfcf1-8a3a-4a45-a9f1-a9b8946b4cdb"],
 " with ",
 Cell["\"Filter.maxDifference\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "20d44bcf-247d-cf49-9071-1bd51c44e0fc"],
 " or similar."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"351cb52f-28d6-ac45-a97e-d56ac18d90b5"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEReduceRegions scale",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": The ",
 Cell["scale", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "bce03994-fc5c-8945-aaee-c59fba1b7c1e"],
 " parameter determines the resolution at which pixels are sampled. A larger \
scale is faster but less precise. Match the scale to your data's native \
resolution when possible."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"42faf255-d672-184f-b8b1-e06c9fe5b85e"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEGradient output",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Returns a two-band image with bands ",
 Cell["\"x\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "eb41e640-73d8-934c-ad4f-29b4e9b5d55e"],
 " (horizontal gradient) and ",
 Cell["\"y\"", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "0627a99d-3631-974c-9c70-aad7cc8699d4"],
 " (vertical gradient). To compute gradient magnitude, use ",
 Cell["GEEExpression", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "f540baaa-b799-6040-aa27-b8c9c918dbc0"],
 " or combine ",
 Cell["GEEPow", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "ee30ac34-4b3b-e041-ad8b-443b25ea0764"],
 " and ",
 Cell["GEESqrt", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "65782313-7948-fc40-b2b2-ebd0d59b9ee1"],
 "."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"74e65537-7041-c748-ac58-b4cef924c4b8"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["GEEEntropy input",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ": Works best on integer-valued or classified images. For continuous data, \
consider binning values first (e.g., with ",
 Cell["GEEMultiply", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "8fae678c-3413-e24f-b162-87a0214b14f8"],
 " and ",
 Cell["GEEToInt", "InlineCode",ExpressionUUID->
  "917c07e4-4844-6d48-8404-38f7bf2a21ca"],
 ")."
}], "Item",ExpressionUUID->"5ee567af-df93-4f4d-9945-3eaa39f536a2"]
}, Open  ]],

